            ),
            4 => 
            array (
                'id' => 5,
                'name' => 'House Boechoute',
                'address' => 'Markt 15',
                'lat' => '51.20851598726573',
                'lng' => '3.223791092982248',
                'description_a' => '<p>House Boechoute is the oldest house on the main square and dates back to 1477.</p>',
                'description_b' => '<p>On the roof you can see a golden metal flag that is connected to a giant compass needle. This device was installed in 1682 to indicate the direction of the wind to the merchants on the square.</p><p>The golden globe is another scientific instrument that is a bit more modern. It was installed in 1837 at the time when the railway line between Brussels and Bruges was being completed and there was a need to align the clocks in all Belgian train stations. For this reason, the exact meridian of 41 places in Belgium was determined by way of a sphere. At noon exactly, the sun’s shadow aligned with a small hole in the globe and fell upon a meridian line in the pavement. The line that was thus drawn can still be traced today thanks to a string of copper nails in the pavement. Of the 41 such devices that were used in Belgium, this is the last surviving one.</p>',
