            ),
            12 => 
            array (
                'id' => 13,
                'name' => 'Saint Elisabeth Church',
                'address' => 'Begijnhof B',
                'lat' => '51.201248180406274',
                'lng' => '3.2231552963008414',
                'description_a' => '<p>The first church on this site dates back to 1245 and burned down in 1584.</p>',
                'description_b' => '<p>The Gothic replacement was built in 1605 and the current Baroque features were added a century later. The church is dedicated to Saint Elisabeth of Hungary, the patron of many beguinages in the Low Countries, whose devotion to the poor made her an enduring symbol of Christian charity. Every day, the few remaining Benedictine sisters ring the bells to announce the start of the daily psalms at noon and vespers at 16.30.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>',
